A mother and her 2-year-old son were declared dead after they were involved in a collision on the R61 in Margate on the Kwa Zulu-Natal South Coast on Sunday. Netcare 911 said it responded to reports of a collision at about 15:00. "Two people from the one car, an adult female and a 2-year-old male, sustained fatal injuries when they were ejected in the crash. Both were declared deceased on the scene," Netcare spokesperson Shawn Herbst said in a statement. The passenger in the second vehicle sustained moderate injuries. She was treated on the scene and later transported to hospital for further medical care. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24Â on Twitter  